{"name": "flask-dramatiq", "metadata": {"name": "flask-dramatiq", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "home_page": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-dramatiq", "license": "BSD-3-Clause", "documentation_url": "https://flask-dramatiq.rtfd.io", "dependencies": ["dramatiq"], "summary": "Adds Dramatiq support to your Flask application", "upload_time": 1573038883}, "documentation": ["![Flask-Dramatiq](https://gitlab.com/bersace/flask-dramatiq/raw/master/docs/logo-horizontal.png?inline=false)\n\nFlask-Dramatiq plugs [Dramatiq](https://dramatiq.io) task queue in your\n[Flask](https://flask.pocoo.org) web application.\n\n## // Features // \n\n- Configure Dramatiq from Flask configuration.\n- Ensure Flask app is available to Dramatiq actor.\n- Add `worker` command to Flask CLI.\n- Enable [Flask Application factory](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/dev/tutorial/factory/).\n- Handle multiple brokers with configurable prefix.\n- Integrates [periodiq](https://gitlab.com/bersace/periodiq). *Optionnal*.\n\nFull documentation at\n[flask-dramatiq.readthedocs.io](https://flask-dramatiq.readthedocs.io).\n\n\n## // Installation and Usage //\n\nFlask-Dramatiq is licensed under BSD-3-Clause. Add `flask-dramatiq` to your\nproject:\n\n``` console\n$ poetry add flask-dramatiq\n```\n\nThen use `Dramatiq` object as a regular Flask extension:\n\n``` python\nfrom flask import Flask\nfrom flask_dramatiq import Dramatiq\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\ndramatiq = Dramatiq(app)\n\n@dramatiq.actor()\ndef my_actor():\n    ...\n\n@app.route(\"/\")\ndef myhandler():\n    my_actor.send()\n```\n\nFlask-Dramatiq adds two configuration keys:\n\n- `DRAMATIQ_BROKER`, points to broker class like\n  `dramatiq.brokers.rabbitmq.RabbitmqBroker` or\n  `dramatiq.brokers.redis.RedisBroker`.\n- `DRAMATIQ_BROKER_URL` is passed as `url` keyword argument to broker class.\n\nNow run worker program to consume messages and execute tasks in the background:\n\n``` console\n$ flask worker --processes=1\n```\n\nA complete flask app is available in project source tree\n[example.py](https://gitlab.com/bersace/flask-dramatiq/blob/master/example.py).\n\n\n## // Credit and Support //\n\nFeel free to open an issue or suggest a merge request on [Gitlab project\npage](https://gitlab.com/bersace/flask-dramatiq). Contribution welcome!\n\nThe project is based on\n[Bogdanp/flask_dramatiq_example](https://github.com/Bogdanp/flask_dramatiq_example).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq.guess_code_directory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "broker", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.import_object", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.format_actor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "actor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.list_managed_actors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "broker", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "queues", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.periodiq", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "broker_name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Run periodiq scheduler.\n\nSetup Dramatiq with broker and task modules from Flask app."]}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.worker", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "processes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "threads", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "queues", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "broker_name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Run dramatiq workers.\n\nSetup Dramatiq with broker and task modules from Flask app.\n\n\b\nexamples:\n  # Run dramatiq with 1 thread per process.\n  $ flask worker --threads 1\n\n\b\n  # Listen only to the \"foo\" and \"bar\" queues.\n  $ flask worker -Q foo,bar\n\n\b\n  # Consuming from a specific broker\n  $ flask worker mybroker"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware", "bases": ["Middleware"], "methods": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware.before_process_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "broker", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware.after_process_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "broker", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "result", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "exception", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware.state", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.AppContextMiddleware.after_skip_message", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.Dramatiq", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "flask_dramatiq.Dramatiq.cron", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flask_dramatiq.Dramatiq.__init__", "asynchronous": fal